snippet.textDisplay: I feel like parents should raise their kids with their birth gender, otherwise they can end up confused and depressed not knowing who they are. I feel as though it’s better to learn who you are as you grow up. I fully support the LGBTQ+ community, I just feel like parents shouldn’t focus so much on raising their kid with “no gender” because that can cause them to have serious mental problems and problems finding out who they are. This whole story seems so forced & people should be able to figure out who they are naturally not by growing up with parents who declare “sex doesn’t define gender.” their hearts were in the right place, but the way they did things is not how I would think to raise my child.
